### Results

Development of the tool, including features and visual function, were informed by a series of meetings with the E2A and Pathfinder teams in DC as well as focus groups in the field conducted by the E2A team. The focus groups provided valuable user testing insights which H&oslash;st used to continue iterating and refining the tool through its beta release. The finished application was well received by E2A, Pathfinder, and USAID teams and their partners, and continues to operate today, providing partners all over the world with valuable insights on youth-focused family planning.

